trans-unit.source: The exception that is thrown when multiple filters match, but only one was expected.
The list of filters includes the filters that caused the exception to be thrown.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MultipleFilterMatchesException"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MultipleFilterMatchesException"></xref> class with a specified error message.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MultipleFilterMatchesException"></xref> class with serialization information and streaming context specified.
The <xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationInfo"></xref> that contains all the data required to serialize the exception.
The <xref href="System.Runtime.Serialization.StreamingContext"></xref> that specifies the source and destination of the stream.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MultipleFilterMatchesException"></xref> class with a specified error message and a collection of filters.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MultipleFilterMatchesException"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MultipleFilterMatchesException"></xref> class with a specified error message, an exception, and a collection of filters.
Gets the collection of filters that caused the exception to be thrown.

The <xref href="System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection`1"></xref> of type <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Dispatcher.MessageFilter"></xref> that contains the filters that caused the exception to be thrown.
